=head1 NAME

hpiwdt -  This sample openhpi application reads and enables the watchdog timer. 

=head1 SYNOPSIS 

hpiwdt [-D domain] [-derx -t sec]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

hpiwdt reads and enables the watchdog timer. 

If no domain is selected, hpiwdt uses a session with the default domain. The selected domain id must be configured via the openhpidclient.conf file specified in the environment.


=head1 OPTIONS

=over 2

 -D domainid  selects the domain
 -e           enables the watchdog timer
 -d           disables the watchdog timer
 -r           resets the watchdog timer
 -t N         sets timeout to N seconds
 -x           show eXtra debug messages

=back

